Column Aliasing
---------------
-An alias is a temporary name assigned to a table or a column in a query.
-Alias is temporary and only exists for the duration of the query.
-Alias name can be given after column name with or without AS key word. 
-If alias name contains multiple words, then enclosed with in double quote 
 or single quote or back tick because space is not allowed in name. 

Example#2:
Show ‚Äúdepartment‚Äù as ‚ÄúDept‚Äù and ‚Äúhire_date‚Äù as ‚ÄúJoining_Date‚Äù.

Sql:
    SELECT first_name AS Emp_Name, salary AS Money FROM employees;
    | Emp_Name  | Money |
